o%20carry%20out%20its%20duties%20by%20excessively%20delaying%20the%20consideration%20of%20bills%20that%20the%20Assembly%20has%20passed%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Punjab%20government%2C%20led%20by%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%2C%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fchandigarh%2Fpunjab-government-supreme-court-governor-banwarilal-purohit-approval-2-bills-9008618%2F%5C%22%3Erecently%20moved%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20top%20court%20against%20governor%20Banwarilal%20Purohit.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fkerala%2Fkerala-government-moves-supreme-court-against-governor-arif-mohammed-khan-over-pending-bills%2Farticle67488446.ece%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Kerala%20government%20raised%20the%20demand%20in%20a%20special%20leave%20petition%20on%20Thursday%2C%20November%202.%20The%20petition%20says%20the%20governor%20%E2%80%9Csubverted%20the%20Constitution%20and%20acted%20in%20a%20manifestly%20arbitrary%20manner%20by%20keeping%20the%20Bills%20passed%20by%20the%20State%20Legislature%20for%20an%20indefinite%20period%E2%80%9D.%20It%20sought%20a%20declaration%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20the%20governor%20is%20duty-bound%20to%20dispose%20of%20every%20Bill%20presented%20to%20him%20%E2%80%9Cwithin%20a%20reasonable%20time%E2%80%9D%20and%20a%20direction%20to%20Khan%20to%20do%20the%20same%20without%20any%20further%20delay.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20newspaper%2C%20three%20Bills%20passed%20by%20the%20legislature%20were%20pending%20with%20the%20governor%20for%20more%20than%20two%20years%20and%20three%20more%20for%20longer%20than%20a%20year.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20conduct%20of%20the%20Governor%20threatened%20to%20defeat%20and%20subvert%20the%20very%20fundamentals%20and%20basic%20foundations%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20including%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20democratic%20good%20governance%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20petition%20argues.%3C%2Fp%