nts%20that%20might%20exonerate%20her.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGive%20us%20the%20one%20really%20bad%20email%20and%20don't%20give%20us%20something%20else%2C%26quot%3B%20Spiro%20said%20in%20court%2C%20describing%20the%20government's%20protocol.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20how%20this%20case%20should%20proceed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAssistant%20U.S.%20Attorney%20Dina%20McLeod%20argued%20that%20the%20government%20was%20fair%20in%20sharing%20its%20evidence%20with%20the%20defense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20emails%2C%20if%20we%20have%20them%2C%20they%20have%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJudge%20Alvin%20K.%20Hellerstein%20ruled%20that%20in%20a%20handful%20of%20instances%20where%20specific%20emails%20were%20referenced%20in%20the%20complaint%2C%20the%20government%20needed%20to%20compel%20JP%20Morgan%20Chase%20to%20produce%20all%20emails%20in%20those%20chains%2C%20and%20all%20documents%20cited%20within.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20government%20is%20to%20require%20JP%20Morgan%20Chase%20to%20review%20its%20files%20and%20to%20assure%20that%20all%20parts%20of%20the%20chain%20in%20which%20these%20emails%20are%20a%20part%20have%20been%20provided%2C%20and%20all%20documents%20referenced%2C%26quot%3B%20Judge%20Hellerstein%20said%20from%20the%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%20the%20judge%20ruled%20against%20the%20defense's%20request%20that%20the%20government%20compel%20the%20financial%20behemoth%20to%20turn%20over%20additional%20emails%20from%20specific%20employees%20referenced%20in%20the%20complaint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpiro%20and%20a%20lawyer%20for%20Javice%20co-defendant%20Olivier%20Amar%2C%20Sean%20Buckley%2C%20said%20they%20soon%20would%20file%20a%20subpoena%20to%20get%20those%20additional%20emails%2C%20based%20on%20a%20different%20legal%20rule%20than%20the%20one%20they%20used%20to%20argue%20in%20court%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpiro%20repeated%20that%20he%20sought%2C%20%26quot%3Ball%20communications%20around%20all%20communications%26quot%3B%20that%20they%20saw%20fit%20to%20quote%20in%20their%20accusation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJudge%20Hellerstein%20warned%20that%20the%20defense's%20broad%20requests%20for%20documents%20was%20appropriate%20for%20a%20civil%20case%2C%20not%20a%20criminal%20one.%20He%20set%20a%20date%20for%20both%20sides%20to%20meet%20again%20in%20court%20on%20January%2017%2C%202024%20to%20work%20out%20further%20scheduling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20set%20October%2028%2C%202024%20as%20a%20trial%20start%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20a%20Delaware%20judge%20ruled%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcharlie-javice-jpmorgan-legal-bills-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJP%20Morgan%20Chase%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20violating%20a%20commitment%20that%20it%20made%20upon%20acquiring%20Frank%20to%20pay%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20Javice's%20legal%20bills.%20Her%20lawyers%20say%20that%20JP%20Morgan%20Chase%20owes%20them%20%24835%2C000%20of%20the%20around%20%243.8%20million%20they%20have%20so%20far%20charged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffrank-founder-charlie-javice-jp-morgan-fraud-trial-date-evidence-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698967426000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652c0e6455f52b01b35fe1be%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffrank-founder-charlie-javice-jp-morgan-fraud-trial-date-evidence-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Charlie%20Javice's%20fraud%20trial%20start%20date%20is%20set.%20The%20judge%20also%20sided%20with%20the%20Frank%20founder's%20lawyers%2C%20ruling%20that%20JP%20Morgan%20must%20offer%20more%20evidence.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Nate%20Schweber)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffrank-founder-charlie-javice-jp-morgan-fraud-trial-date-evidence-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20volunteered%20in%20Ukraine%20when%20Russia%20invaded%20and%20in%20Israel%20when%20Hamas%20attacked.%20In%20Ukraine%2C%20I%20saved%20lives.%20In%20Israel%2C%20I%20collected%20bodies.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22side-by-side%20photos%20of%20Valerie%20Dyksztejn%20volunteering%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20in%20Israel%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6543fcf4b788914e554f2de0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EValerie%20Dyksztejn%20volunteered%20with%20ZAKA%20in%20both%20Ukraine%20(left)%20when%20Russia%20invaded%20in%20February%202022%20and%20in%20Israel%20(right)%20when%20Hamas%20attacked%20last%20month.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Valerie%20Dyksztejn%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EValerie%20Dyksztejn%20is%20a%20Ukrainian-Israeli%20woman%20and%20volunteer%20with%20Jewish%20rescue%20organization%20ZAKA.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDyksztejn%20was%20living%20in%20Kyiv%20when%20Russia%20invaded%20and%20vacationing%20in%20Israel%20when%20Hamas%20attacked.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20said%20she%20helped%20save%20lives%20in%20Ukraine.%20But%20there%20were%20no%20happy%20endings%20in%20Israel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20story%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Valerie%20Dyksztejn%2C%20a%2043-year-old%20Ukrainian-Israeli%20woman%20who%20was%20living%20in%20Kyiv%20when%20Russia%20invaded%20Ukraine%20in%20February%202022%20and%20was%20vacationing%20in%20Israel%20when%20Hamas%20attacked%20in%20October.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDyksztejn%20is%20an%20emergency%20response%20volunteer%20with%20ZAKA%2C%20an%20Israel-based%20collection%20of%20voluntary%20community%20emergency%20response%20teams%20whose%20members%20are%20primarily%20Jewish.%20ZAKA%20also%20provides%20rapid%20response%20to%20disasters%20around%20the%20world%2C%20including%20in%20Ukraine.%C2%A0Dyksztejn%20volunteered%20with%20ZAKA%20in%20both%20the%20Ukraine%20and%20Israel%20wars.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20born%20in%20Kyiv%20and%20my%20family%20and%20I%20immigrated%20to%20Israel%20in%20the%2090s.%20We%20lived%20near%20the%20Gaza%20border.%20I%20know%20the%20area%20very%20well.%20I%20grew%20up%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20left%20young%20and%20was%20recruited%20to%20the%20Israeli%20military.%20I%20had%20a%20computer-job%20in%20the%20army.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20army%20I%20went%20to%20study%20and%20got%20married.%20My%20husband%20is%20Belgian.%20We%20have%20five%20children%20and%20three%20grandchildren.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20got%20married%20we%20first%20lived%20in%20Israel%2C%20but%20we%20worked%20in%20Ukraine.%20We%20traveled%20a%20lot%20back%20and%20forth%20between%20Israel%20and%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20we%20moved%20to%20Ukraine%20permanently.%20Most%20of%20my%20kids%20still%20live%20in%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20volunteering%20for%20ZAKA%20wasn't%20intensive.%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20spoke%20a%20lot%20of%20languages%20and%20it%20was%20mostly%20tourists%20in%20Ukraine%20asking%20for%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWherever%20Jews%20are%2C%20we%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20when%20the%20war%20started%2C%20it%20took%20a%20dramatic%20turn.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20started%2C%20we%20were%20in%20Kyiv.%20We%20didn't%20leave%20our%20home%20for%20the%20first%20few%20days.%20It's%20not%20easy%20to%20leave%20a%20home%2C%20to%20leave%20a%20business%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20left%20only%20when%20the%20tanks%20were%20really%20outside%20Kyiv%2C%20in%20the%20last%20convoy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20go%20to%20Antwerp%2C%20Belgium%2C%20because%20that's%20where%20my%20husband%20is%20from.%20We%20thought%20we%20would%20go%20for%20two%20weeks%20until%20things%20calmed%20down%20and%20then%20would%20go%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20traveled%20through%20Moldova.%20It%20took%20us%20about%2040%20hours%20to%20get%20to%20the%20border.%20When%20we%20finally%20got%20to%20Moldova%2C%20it%20was%20insane.%20The%20chaos%20there%20was%20crazy.%20I%20can't%20explain%20the%20amount%20of%20people%20that%20were%20there.%20There%20were%20no%20places%20to%20sleep.%20Everything%20was%20occupied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Valerie%20Dyksztejn%20wearing%20a%20yellow%20emergency%20response%20vest%20and%20helmet%20at%20the%20scene%20of%20destruction%20in%20Israel%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6543fde936d588dc55c9acb6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHamas%20militants%20attacked%20thousands%20of%20people%20at%20an%20outdoor%20Israeli%20music%20festival%20in%20the%20desert%20on%20Oct.%207.%20ZAKA%20later%20said%20it%20recovered%20260%20bodies%20at%20the%20site%20of%20the%20festival.%20%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Valerie%20Dyksztejn%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20just%20needed%20help%2C%20so%20we%20tried%20to%20help%20as%20much%20as%20we%20could.%20After%20a%20few%20days%20ZAKA%20opened%20a%2024%2F7%20call%20center.%20We%20decided%20to%20stay%20in%20Moldova%20and%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20managed%20to%20open%20a%20hotel%20that%20was%20converted%20into%20a%20place%20that%20provided%20medical%20attention%20to%20people%20who%20stayed%20there.%20We%20were%20getting%20people%20out%20on%20planes%2C%20the%20badly%20injured%2C%20and%20people%20who%20couldn't%20move%20by%20themselves.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoldova-operation-rescue-ukraine-holocaust-survivors-chabad-israel-jewish-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20lot%20of%20them%20were%20Holocaust%20survivors.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Ukraine%20there%20are%20not%20many%20Jewish%20families%20left%2C%20and%20the%20Holocaust%20survivors%20are%20mostly%20completely%20alone.%20Their%20caregivers%20left%20and%20ran%20when%20the%20war%20started.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20ran%20the%20hotel%20in%20Moldova%20for%20eight%20months.%20Most%20of%20the%20requests%20for%20help%20were%20from%20Jews%2C%20but%20we%20also%20helped%20ethnically%20Ukrainian%20people.%20Anyone%20who%20reached%20out%2C%20we%20tried%20to%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20eight%20months%2C%20the%20demand%20slowed%20down%20and%20there%20was%20no%20longer%20a%20need%20for%20a%20full%20hotel%20to%20operate.%20We%20closed%20the%20hotel%20and%20returned%20home%20to%20Kyiv.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20met%20amazing%20people%20with%20so%20many%20different%20stories.%20I%20am%20so%20proud%20of%20the%20opportunity%20I%20was%20given%20to%20do%20that.%20It's%20unfortunate%20that%20it%20happened%20under%20those%20sad%20circumstances%2C%20but%20I%20am%20proud%20of%20this%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20helped%20more%20than%20100%20Holocaust%20survivors%20who%20were%20not%20mobile.%20Most%20of%20them%20went%20to%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbout%20a%20month%20ago%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20go%20on%20vacation%20to%20Israel.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20went%20to%20celebrate%20the%20Sukkot%20holiday%20with%20our%20children.%20We%20saw%20friends%20and%20had%20fun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20staying%20with%20my%20daughter%20in%20Bet%20Shemesh%20that%20weekend.%20The%20air%20raid%20alarm%20woke%20us%20up%20at%206%3A30%20a.m.%20We%20got%20up%20and%20looked%20at%20each%20other.%20We%20knew%20something%20was%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20in%20the%20Gaza%20envelope%2C%20so%20the%20alarms%20are%20not%20special%20for%20me%3B%20And%20I%20already%20went%20through%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20Bet%20Shemesh%2C%20the%20air%20raid%20alarms%20are%20not%20a%20usual%20thing.%20I%20can't%20remember%20the%20last%20time%20before%20this%20one%20when%20there%20were%20rockets%20in%20Bet%20Shemesh.%20This%20is%20not%20something%20that%20happens%20often.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Valerie%20Dyksztejn%20standing%20with%20two%20other%20ZAKA%20volunteers%20amidst%20rubble%20in%20Israel.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6543fe7eb788914e554f2ffd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBet%20Shemesh%2C%20located%20in%20the%20west%20of%20Israel's%20Jerusalem%20District%2C%20is%20about%2040%20miles%20from%20the%20nearest%20site%20of%20Hamas%20attacks%20on%20Oct.%207.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Valerie%20Dyksztejn%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20religious%20and%20keep%20Shabbat%2C%20so%20our%20phones%20were%20off%20and%20we%20couldn't%20really%20understand%20what%20was%20going%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20took%20his%20ZAKA%20walkie-talkie%20with%20him%20from%20Ukraine.%20I%20left%20mine%20at%20home%20because%20I%20thought%20we%20wouldn't%20need%20it%20while%20on%20vacation%20in%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20started%20getting%20messages%20on%20the%20radio.%20They%20asked%20for%20anyone%20who%20could%20come%20help%20to%20report.%20So%20we%20put%20on%20our%20yellow%20vests%20and%20started%20driving%2C%20not%20really%20knowing%20where%20we%20were%20going%20at%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20sent%20us%20to%20Barzilai%20Hospital%20in%20Ashkelon.%20I%20was%20helping%20catalog%20the%20bodies%20while%20my%20husband%20was%20helping%20take%20fingerprints.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20bit%20later%2C%20ZAKA%20was%20looking%20for%20volunteers%20to%20go%20to%20the%20area%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-music-festival-hamas-photographer-captured-moments-joy-before-attack-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20music%20festival%20was%3C%2Fa%3E.%20My%20husband%20volunteered%20immediately.%20He%20and%20I%20are%20working%20together%2C%20volunteering%20together.%20To%20this%20day%2C%20we%20have%20done%20everything%20together.%20So%20I%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20coming%20with%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20in%20this%20area%2C%20I%20know%20every%20turn%20and%20every%20tree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20got%20in%20an%20ambulance%20and%20went.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%20we%20thought%20we%20were%20going%20to%20help%20people%20who%20were%20injured%2C%20but%20after%20we%20passed%20Ashkelon%2C%20we%20started%20seeing%20bodies%20on%20the%20road.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20got%20closer%20to%20a%20shelter%20on%20the%20side%20of%20the%20road%2C%20we%20saw%20an%20unimaginable%20sight.%20The%20amount%20of%20bodies%20inside%20the%20shelter%E2%80%A6%20they%20were%20thrown%20one%20on%20top%20of%20the%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20no%20words%20to%20describe%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20we%20got%20to%20the%20music%20festival%20area%2C%20we%20thought%20we%20had%20seen%20everything.%20But%20we%20hadn't%20seen%20anything%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20responsible%20for%20finding%20any%20kind%20of%20markers%20to%20identify%20people%2C%20cutting%20bags%2C%20and%20looking%20for%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20help%20volunteers%20when%20they%20reached%20a%20breaking%20point.%20I%20don't%20know%20how%20I%20had%20the%20power%20to%20do%20this.%20We%20had%20to%20call%20for%20backup%20because%20we%20didn't%20have%20enough%20people%20to%20deal%20with%20that%20amount%20of%20bodies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Valerie%20Dyksztejn%20is%20comforted%20by%20another%20ZAKA%20volunteer.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6543ff04b788914e554f303d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIsraeli%20officials%20said%20more%20than%201%2C400%20people%20were%20killed%20since%20the%20Hamas%20attacks%20on%20October%207%20and%20more%20than%20100%20Israelis%20were%20initially%20taken%20hostage.%20The%20Gaza%20Health%20Ministry%20said%20this%20week%20that%20more%20than%208%2C800%20Palestinians%2C%20including%20more%20than%203%2C600%20children%20have%20been%20killed%20as%20a%20result%20of%20Israel's%20response.%20%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Valerie%20Dyksztejn%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20you%20can%20do%20at%20that%20moment%20is%20show%20these%20people%20a%20final%20sign%20of%20respect.%20There%20is%20nothing%20you%20can%20do%20beyond%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20day%2C%20when%20we%20already%20thought%20we%20had%20seen%20everything%2C%20we%20went%20inside%20people's%20homes.%20This%20was%20even%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20first%20night%20we%20slept%20in%20our%20car%20for%20two%20or%20three%20hours%20and%20then%20we%20went%20back.%20It%20felt%20like%20it%20would%20never%20end.%20Two%20full%20weeks%20and%20we%20only%20saw%20bodies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20person%20behind%20every%20single%20body.%20There%20are%20no%20words%20that%20can%20describe%20that.%20It%20was%20the%20most%20horrific%20thing%20a%20person%20could%20imagine.%20The%20worst%20of%20nightmares.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20returned%20to%20Kyiv%20last%20Thursday%20after%20three%20weeks.%20Our%20heart%20is%20broken.%20Our%20heart%20is%20there%20in%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERight%20now%2C%20I%20feel%20more%20safe%20in%20Kyiv.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKyiv%20is%20safer%20than%20Israel%20right%20now.%20But%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20you%20can't%20compare%20the%20two%20wars.%20They%20are%20very%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20prepared%20me%20well%20to%20help%20people%20evacuate.%20I%20built%20resilience%20to%20see%20hard%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20difference%20between%20Israel%20and%20Ukraine%20was%20that%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20I%20helped%20rescue%20people%20who%20were%20still%20alive.%20We%20mostly%20had%20happy%20endings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Israel's%20case%2C%20I%20packed%20bags%20with%20bodies.%20There%20were%20no%20happy%20endings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sights%20we%20saw%20were%20hard%2C%20but%20we%20are%20still%20here%2C%20we%20are%20alive.%20We%20have%20a%20new%20generation%20to%20raise.%20And%20we%20will%20raise%20them%20with%20pride.%20If%20we%20give%20up%2C%20they'll%20win.%20The%20Jewish%20people%20are%20not%20the%20people%20who%20give%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETranslations%20by%20Alisa%20Shodiyev%20Kaff%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukrainian-israeli-woman-volunteered-in-both-russia-and-hamas-wars-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698967082000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6543fd663cc84b4dfafb50c3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukrainian-israeli-woman-volunteered-in-both-russia-and-hamas-wars-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Valerie%20Dyksztejn%20was%20living%20in%20Kyiv%20when%20Russia%20invaded%20Ukraine%20and%20vacationing%20in%20Israel%20when%20Hamas%20attacked.%20She%20volunteered%20in%20both%20wars.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22akaff%40insider.com%20(Alisa%20Shodiyev%20Kaff%2CErin%20Snodgrass)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A34%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukrainian-israeli-woman-volunteered-in-both-russia-and-hamas-wars-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Influential%20Democrat%20calls%20Israel's%20relentless%20strikes%20on%20Gaza%20'unacceptable%20and%20unsustainable'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Democratic%20Sen.%20Chris%20Murphy%20of%20Connecticut%20at%20the%20Capitol%20on%20March%2016%2C%202022.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63f7ae846e91cc0018df5376%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDemocratic%20Sen.%20Chris%20Murphy%20of%20Connecticut%20at%20the%20Capitol%20on%20March%2016%2C%202022.%3Cp%3EBi