0home%20and%20information%20technology%20ministries%20in%20probing%20the%20allegation%20against%20Moitra.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDubey%20along%20with%20a%20lawyer%2C%20Jai%20Anant%20Dehadrai%20%E2%80%93%20termed%20by%20Moitra%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98jilted%20ex%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20had%20filed%20the%20complaint%20with%20the%20committee%20alleging%20that%20the%20TMC%20MP%20had%20accepted%20bribes%20from%20Dubai-based%20businessman%20Darshan%20Hiranandani%20to%20ask%20questions%20in%20parliament.%20The%20complaint%20said%20Moitra%20had%20shared%20the%20password%20of%20the%20official%20email%20of%20her%20Lok%20Sabha%20account%20with%20Hiranandani%2C%20claiming%20it%20had%20compromised%20%E2%80%98national%20security%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMoitra%2C%20a%20vocal%20critic%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20had%20shot%20back%20at%20Dubey%2C%20stating%20that%20his%20complaint%20was%20because%20of%20her%20questioning%20him%20in%20parliament%20about%20a%20fake%20degree%20he%20allegedly%20submitted%20along%20with%20his%20election%20affidavit%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThursday%E2%80%99s%20meeting%20went%20on%20for%20about%20three%20hours%2C%20ending%20in%20a%20walkout%20not%20just%20by%20Moitra%20but%20also%20by%20five%20members%20belonging%20to%20the%20opposition%20parties.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20was%20because%20she%20was%20asked%20irrelevant%2C%20indecent%20and%20unethical%20questions.%20We%20objected%20that%20such%20questions%20should%20not%20be%20asked%20by%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20member%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Asked%20what%20those%20questions%20were%2C%20the%20member%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CShe%20was%20asked%20which%20hotel%20in%20Dubai%20she%20had%20stayed%20during%20her%20visits%20and%20with%20whom%2C%20etc.%20Opposition%20members%20found%20those%20questions%20posed%20to%20a%20woman%20member%20of%20parliament%20in%20an%20official%20platform%20very%20offensive%20and%20walked%20out%20of%20it.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20member%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20the%20meeting%20started%2C%20the%20chairperson%20began%20asking%20her%20questions%20written%20on%20a%20paper.%20What%20was%20surprising%20was%20that%20even%20after%20she%20had%20said%20a%20%E2%80%98no%E2%80%99%20to%20the%20primary%20question%2C%20parts%20of%20the%20questions%20already%20written%20on%20that%20paper%20were%20also%20asked%20by%20him%2C%20as%20if%20it%20was%20a%20task%20given%20to%20him%20that%20he%20had%20to%20mandatorily%20complete.%20Then%2C%20some%20members%20objected%20to%20the%20meeting%20starting%20with%20the%20chairperson%20questioning%20her%20because%20in%20the%20previous%20meeting%2C%20when%20Dubey%20and%20Dehadrai%20were%20called%20to%20depose%2C%20they%20were%20given%20an%20opportunity%20to%20present%20their%20opening%20statement.%20Finally%2C%20she%20was%20allowed%20to%20read%20out%20her%20statement.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20other%20member%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThroughout%20her%20statement%2C%20she%20had%20highlighted%20that%20the%20complaint%20has%20stemmed%20from%20a%20personal%20fight%20(between%20her%20and%20Dehadrai).%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAsked%20if%20she%20had%20shared%20her%20password%20with%20Hiranandani%2C%20Moitra%20admitted%20to%20taking%20help%20from%20his%20personal%20staff%20to%20file%20questions%20in%20parliament.%20%E2%80%9CTo%20this%2C%20some%20members%20pointed%20out%20to%20the%20chairperson%20that%20most%20MPs%20take%20help%20from%20others%20to%20file%20questions%20online%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20member%20related.%20All%20the%20questions%20posed%20to%20the%20TMC%20were%20only%20by%20the%20chairperson%20and%20no%20other%20member%20was%20allowed%20to%20