-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunderprivileged%20girls%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewho%20were%20either%20lost%2C%20abducted%20or%20dumped%20to%20lead%20an%20empowered%20life%20of%20independence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFor%20those%20who%20have%20no%20one%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EDr%20Michelle%20takes%20her%20inspiration%20from%20her%20grandmother%2C%20who%20was%20a%20Jewish%20immigrant%20in%20the%20USA%20from%20Russia.%20She%20was%20hired%20by%20the%20National%20Council%20of%20Jewish%20Women%20to%20serve%20as%20an%20assistant%20immigrant%20arrival%20agent.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20working%20at%20Ellis%20Island%20in%20the%20US%2C%20her%20grandmother%20ensured%20that%20young%20Jewish%20immigrants%20went%20to%20their%20actual%20relatives%20instead%20of%20falling%20into%20a%20trafficking%20ring.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShe%20recounts%20how%20her%20grandma%20also%20used%20to%20tell%20her%20stories%20of%20the%20starving%20children%20of%20the%20Great%20Chinese%20Famine%20in%201958.%20%E2%80%9CShe%20told%20me%20never%20to%20forget%20them%2C%20and%20when%20I%20saw%20how%20the%20Korean%20War%20led%20to%20orphans%20in%20the%20country%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20dedicate%20my%20life%20to%20caring%20for%20these%20children.%20This%20was%20an%20epiphany%20for%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20tells%3Cstrong%3E%20The%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20Dr%20Michelle%20already%20had%20a%20biological%20daughter%2C%20she%20adopted%20another%20infant%20girl%20from%20Kolkata%20in%201984.%20I%20always%20knew%20that%20somewhere%20there%20was%20a%20child%20out%20there%20and%20I%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20raising%20her%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20she%20raised%20her%20children%20in%20the%20US%2C%20she%20always%20kept%20them%20connected%20with%20Indian%20culture.%20In%201999%2C%20after%20getting%20diagnosed%20with%20breast%20cancer%2C%20she%20moved%20to%20Kolkata%20to%20live%20with%20her%20adopted%20daughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%20